Pakistan, Yusuf describes the potential for third-party intervention to avert nuclear war. This book lays out the ways regional powers behave and maneuver in response to the pressures of strong global powers. Moving beyond debates surrounding the widely accepted rational deterrence model, Yusuf offers an original perspective rooted in thoughtful analysis of recent regional nuclear conflicts. With depth and insight, Brokering Peace in Nuclear Environments urges the international community to rethink its approach to nuclear deterrence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCrisis managementzUnited States. 0aNuclear crisis controlzSouth Asia. 0aNuclear warfarezIndiaxPrevention. 0aNuclear warfarezPakistanxPrevention. 0aNuclear warfarezPakistanzPāṭaxPrevention. 4aIndia. 4aPakistan. 4aSouth Asia. 4aUnited States. 4abrokered bargaining. 4acrisis management. 4anuclear crisis behavior. 4anuclear deterrence. 4athird party mediation. 4aunipolarity. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503606555zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503606555423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503606555.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles